---

## 🚀 Quick Start

```bash
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p
```

---

## 📊 Quick Reference

### Overview Table

| Concept | Class Pattern | Use Case |
|---------|--------------|----------|
| **Spacing** | `m-{size}`, `p-{size}` | Margin, padding |
| **Flexbox** | `flex`, `items-{align}`, `justify-{align}` | One-dimensional layouts |
| **Grid** | `grid`, `grid-cols-{n}` | Two-dimensional layouts |
| **Colors** | `bg-{color}-{shade}`, `text-{color}-{shade}` | Backgrounds, text |
| **Typography** | `text-{size}`, `font-{weight}` | Text styling |
| **Responsive** | `{breakpoint}:{class}` | Mobile-first design |
| **Dark Mode** | `dark:{class}` | Dark theme support |

### Breakpoints

| Prefix | Min Width | Target |
|--------|-----------|--------|
| (none) | 0px | Mobile first |
| `sm:` | 640px | Small tablets |
| `md:` | 768px | Tablets |
| `lg:` | 1024px | Desktops |
| `xl:` | 1280px | Large screens |
| `2xl:` | 1536px | Extra large |

### Spacing Scale

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `0` | 0px | No spacing |
| `px` | 1px | Hairline |
| `1` | 4px | 0.25rem |
| `2` | 8px | 0.5rem |
| `3` | 12px | 0.75rem |
| `4` | 16px | 1rem |
| `6` | 24px | 1.5rem |
| `8` | 32px | 2rem |

---

## 🎨 Common Patterns

### Spacing

```tsx
// Margin
<div className="m-4 mx-auto mt-8 mb-4">  // all, x, y, bottom

// Padding
<div className="p-4 px-6 py-2">
```

### Flexbox

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
<div className="flex-1">          {/* grow */}
<div className="flex-col">
```

### Grid

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
```

---

## 🌓 Dark Mode

```tsx
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
```

Config:
```js
// tailwind.config.js
export default {
  darkMode: 'class',
  // ...
}
```

---

## 📱 Responsive

```tsx
// Mobile-first
<div className="text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg">

// Hide/Show
<div className="hidden md:block">
<div className="block md:hidden">
```

---

## 🎯 Best Practices

- ✅ Use `@apply` sparingly (prefer inline classes)
- ✅ Extract components with repeated patterns
- ✅ Use `arbitrary values` sparingly: `w-[137px]`
- ✅ Use design tokens for consistent spacing/colors

---

## ✅ Quality Gates

### Validation Checklist

#### CSS Usage
- [ ] **CU1** - Classes utilitaires en ligne (priorité sur `@apply`)
- [ ] **CU2** - `@apply` limité aux composants réutilisables uniquement
- [ ] **CU3** - Styles inline évités (sauf valeurs dynamiques)

#### Design Tokens
- [ ] **DT1** - Valeurs arbitraires limitées (`w-[137px]` → `w-32` ou token)
- [ ] **DT2** - Couleurs définies dans `tailwind.config.ts`
- [ ] **DT3** - Espacement avec échelle standard (`4`, `8`, `12`...)

#### Responsive Design
- [ ] **RD1** - Mobile-first (base styles → `sm:` → `md:` → `lg:`)
- [ ] **RD2** - Breakpoints utilisés de façon cohérente
- [ ] **RD3** - Hide/Show avec `hidden md:block` pattern

#### Theme & Consistency
- [ ] **TC1** - Couleurs du thème utilisées (pas de hardcoded colors)
- [ ] **TC2** - Dark mode implémenté avec préfixe `dark:`
- [ ] **TC3** - Spacing consistant avec design tokens

### Acceptance Criteria

L'implémentation Tailwind est conforme quand :
- **Classes utilitaires** en ligne (pas de `@apply` excessif)
- **Design tokens** définis dans config
- **Responsive** mobile-first
- **Dark mode** fonctionnel
- **Pas de valeurs arbitraires** en production
- **Spécificité CSS** gérée proprement

---

## 🔧 Troubleshooting

| Problem | Cause | Solution |
|---------|-------|----------|
| **"Styles not applying"** | Missing Tailwind directives | Add `@tailwind` directives to CSS |
| **"Dark mode not working"** | Missing `darkMode: 'class'` config | Add to tailwind.config.js |
| **"Custom colors not working"** | Not extended in theme config | Extend theme in tailwind.config.js |
| **"Purge not working"** | Wrong content paths | Update `content` array in config |
| **"Styles removed in build"** | Not in content paths | Add file paths to content array |

